a,\n[174](iml15.htm#page_174).\n\nDuryodhana (door-yo\xc2\xb4dh\xc4\x83n-\xc4\x83), eldest of Kauravas, [177](iml15.htm#page_177);\nattempts to kill youthful Bhima, [178](iml15.htm#page_178) _et seq_.; at the\ntournament, conflict with Bhima, [187](iml16.htm#page_187); Karna\'s coming,\n[189](iml16.htm#page_189) _et seq_.; Karna becomes his ally,\n[193](iml16.htm#page_193) _et seq_.; fails to defeat Drupada,\n[195](iml17.htm#page_195), [196](iml17.htm#page_196); jealous of Yudhishthira,\n[197](iml17.htm#page_197), [198](iml17.htm#page_198); plots to destroy\nPandavas, [199](iml17.htm#page_199); the "house of lac",\n[200](iml17.htm#page_200); believes his rivals are dead,\n[201](iml17.htm#page_201); discovers Pandavas are alive,\n[223](iml18.htm#page_223); Arjuna captures bride-elect of,\n[227](iml19.htm#page_227); at Pandava imperial sacrifice,\n[232](iml19.htm#page_232) _et seq_.; arranges gambling match with Pandavas,\n[237](iml20.htm#page_237) _et seq_.; Shakuni plays for with loaded dice,\n[240](iml20.htm#page_240) _et seq_.; Draupadi won for,\n[240](iml20.htm#page_240) _et seq_.; Pandavas exiled,\n[248](iml20.htm#page_248); Bhima vows to slay, [246](iml20.htm#page_246);\nDraupadi\'s anger against, [251](iml21.htm#page_251) _et seq_.; captured by\nGandharvas, [259](iml21.htm#page_259); rescued by Pandavas,\n[259](iml21.htm#page_259), [260](iml21.htm#page_260); demons promise to help,\n[260](iml21.htm#page_260); the royal sacrifice of, [261](iml21.htm#page_261);\nplots against Pandavas with Karna and Shakuni, [269](iml21.htm#page_269);\ncondemned at meeting of Pandava allies, [270](iml22.htm#page_270) _et seq_.;\ninterviews with Krishna and Balarama, [273](iml22.htm#page_273); elders plead\nwith at Hastinapur, [274](iml22.htm#page_274) _et seq_.; defiant speech of,\n[280](iml22.htm#page_280); plot to seize Krishna, [281](iml22.htm#page_281);\nKarna supports, [282](iml22.htm#page_282), [283](iml22.htm#page_283),\n[284](iml22.htm#page_284); the declaration of war w